before_start: {"blocks":[{"key":"6dhml","text":"Handle rat beforehand to reduce stress","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"ff9cg","text":"Bring rat from vivarium (or wherever it is kept) to surgery room in a clean cage ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
description: {"blocks":[{"key":"cdlqu","text":"protocol describes how to use anesthesia machine with isoflurane to anesthetize a rat. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"skrl","text":"Ensure the anesthesia box that contains the rat has a fully closed and locked lid.  Ensure that the nose cone used to maintain anesthesia is tightly around the rats nose.  Perform procedure in a hood for safety and wear lab coat and gloves.  Turn off the gas flow as soon as you are done using it for anesthesia. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
materials_text: {"blocks":[{"key":"5g87k","text":"Paper towels","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"df8f2","text":"A glove","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"c79hr","text":"Tape ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"b4kgr","text":"Isoflurane cart (Tape, extra isoflurane, oxygen tanks, black wrench to open oxygen tank)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3h1fb","text":"Rat","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"60q5i","text":"Make sure you have a surgery room booked ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"qqs3","text":"Some sort of table or surgical workbench to transfer rat to when fully anesthetized ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f5u65","text":"Grab isoflurane cart and/or supplies and bring it to the surgery room","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ap7fv","text":"Place paper towels in the plastic container ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"11af0","text":"Make sure the tubing is tightly sealed together (if tape is needed add tape)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1t9b7","text":"Make sure all of the tubing is in the correct place and connected","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"73qql","text":"Make sure the valves are parallel with the tubing (the pink and orange tubing)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fctfq","text":"Use larger thicker tape to secure white tubing down onto the surgery table (where you want it on the workbench)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ckotf","text":"Snip open a little hole in a glove and place it over the tubing for the rat's mouth as a nose cone for anesthesia during surgical procedures","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9cbrn","text":"Check isoflurane level (make sure it is between the minimum and maximum fill lines) ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ekf74","text":"If the isoflurane level is low then unscrew the cap and slowly add in the isoflurane ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"bv4kn","text":"Set isoflurane regulator on top-adjust dial as appropriate","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3o16o","text":"Use the black wrench to open the oxygen tank ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"c03uj","text":"Turn to the right to open","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b8gbj","text":"Look at the oxygen regulator and turn the green knob so the silver ball is in the middle of the 1 on the regulator.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2jq7e","text":"Place the rat in the plastic box and close the lid","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ml8i","text":"Adjust isoflurane dial as needed","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9o536","text":"Start at 4 (if female)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5mjb8","text":"Start at 5 (if male), heavier animals usually need more isoflurane to become anesthetized","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6l5qa","text":"Keep rat under for a few minutes or until the rat’s breathing slows down","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9g7gf","text":"Take the rat out of the plastic container and place it onto the surgery table","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eorg","text":"Do a toe pinch using forceps to make sure the animal does not feel any pain","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6kl1j","text":"If the rat has a pain reflex or a jerk motion of the limb then place back into the plastic container and continue anesthesia","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"e8vlr","text":"If the rat has no pain reflex or jerk then continue","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6tte7","text":"Put the tubing that has the glove with the slit over the rat's mouth and nose to maintain anesthesia","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cmto8","text":"Then when the rat is fully anesthetized you can proceed with your surgery","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9nl9m","text":"Turn off the isoflurane dial (back to 0)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8q8rc","text":"Take the black wrench to close the oxygen tank","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5kstm","text":"Turn to the left to close","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"45c75","text":"Check to make sure there is no tubing loose/disconnected","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"b9glo","text":"In case there is a leak","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ftkld","text":"Or if something is not working","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"a6ktn","text":"Adjust dial ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"c492a","text":"More or less isoflurane depending on how the rat is doing ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8oj0g","text":"Press the green oxygen flush button","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1ovf6","text":"This clears out oxygen from the tubing  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fn2cb","text":"Remove the paper towels and dispose of them","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1cjl0","text":"Clean out the plastic box with paper towels and water only","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"d4490","text":"Return isoflurane machine and supplies to its storage place","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1u16m","text":"Place cage where the dirty cages go to be cleaned","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

title: Isoflurane Anesthesia Protocol
warning: {"blocks":[{"key":"9tqls","text":"Make sure at least one of the valves are open","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"7bcku","text":"Always check oxygen levels and isoflurane levels","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"b452s","text":"Turn off isoflurane using the dial when you are not using it","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
